{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01U37Mn7QcaUnDpryDxuFBXd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the source file and convert it to a knowledge file JSON.\n\n**Step 1: Identify the title**\nThe title is: \"出力するHTMLの文字コードを変更したいのですが\"\n\n**Step 1.5: Check for no-knowledge-content**\nThe source contains Layer A and Layer B content (configuration properties, XML examples, class names). So `no_knowledge_content: false`.\n\n**Step 2: Build the section list**\nThis is an RST file. Looking for h2 headings (text followed by `-----` underlines).\n\nLooking at the source... The main heading is `=====` which is h1. \n\nThe document doesn't have any h2 headings—it's structured as a Q&A format with admonitions, so everything goes into a single section.\n\n**Step 3: Extract section content**\n\nThe source addresses how to change HTML character encoding from UTF-8 to Windows-31J, with solutions covering WebFrontController configuration (modifying the `defaultEncoding` property), file download handling through MimeBDownloadFileNameEncoder and UrlDownloadFileNameEncoder, and HttpTestConfiguration for the testing framework.\n\nNow I'm identifying the key layers: the default HTML output uses UTF-8 encoding and requires changes across three configuration points. The specific properties to modify are `defaultEncoding` in WebFrontController, `charset` in both the MIME and URL download encoders, and `htmlResourcesCharset` in HttpTestConfiguration. I'll exclude the reference documentation links since those are just pointers.\n\nWriting the section content... Configuring the MIME-B and URL encoders for download filenames, then setting the character encoding for the HTTP test configuration framework to Windows-31J.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20882,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_inp